1
00:00:01,876 --> 00:00:02,877
I'm sorry.

2
00:00:06,297 --> 00:00:08,049
[JAO] Why are you keeping her from me, Kara?

3
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:09,509
All this time,

4
00:00:09,551 --> 00:00:11,261
you were fooling me all along.

5
00:00:11,302 --> 00:00:13,303
I thought by keeping you away,

6
00:00:13,304 --> 00:00:14,430
I was doing the right thing.

7
00:00:14,431 --> 00:00:15,473
But I was wrong.

8
00:00:15,765 --> 00:00:16,932
[JAO] I want to talk to her.

9
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:18,059
[ALLIE] Hello, Kara?

10
00:00:18,810 --> 00:00:19,602
[JAO] Hello, Allie?

11
00:00:19,603 --> 00:00:22,230
Sorry if I did something to make you do this, but…

12
00:00:22,939 --> 00:00:23,940
can we talk?

13
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:25,734
I think it’s time for you to let go.

14
00:00:25,775 --> 00:00:26,817
Can we at least

15
00:00:26,818 --> 00:00:28,652
see each other one last time?

16
00:00:28,653 --> 00:00:30,238
[CAROL] He didn’t get mad at you?

17
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:31,656
How nice of Jao.

18
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:34,366
If Allie had only talked to him, this would've been over by now.

19
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:36,995
It’s partly my fault things got this bad.

20
00:00:37,036 --> 00:00:38,036
What happened, Pearl?

21
00:00:38,037 --> 00:00:39,121
Nothing, sir!

22
00:00:39,122 --> 00:00:41,124
- Got something in my eye... - Wait, let me see.

23
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:42,541
Jao!

24
00:00:42,542 --> 00:00:44,460
We are going to Pacifico. You wanna surf?

25
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:46,463
No, maybe next time. I need to go somewhere.

26
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:47,588
[JAO] I found Allie.

27
00:00:47,589 --> 00:00:48,881
[SIARGAONON] [MAN] Kara, tell your

28
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:49,841
friend to go home.

29
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:51,885
Poor guy’s been out there for hours.

30
00:00:52,385 --> 00:00:53,219
[KARA] You good?

31
00:00:53,428 --> 00:00:54,512
[JAO] It’s really over, huh?

32
00:00:54,804 --> 00:00:56,181
This is how it ends.

33
00:00:56,473 --> 00:00:58,641
This is where our story ends.

34
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:04,272
Kara, thanks for coming with me.

35
00:01:05,482 --> 00:01:06,483
You're welcome.

36
00:01:08,109 --> 00:01:09,110
Oh, right.

37
00:01:10,069 --> 00:01:11,321
[JAO] Can you do me a favor?

38
00:01:11,362 --> 00:01:12,363
Can you…

39
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,910
give this to Allie?

40
00:01:18,953 --> 00:01:22,332
Please tell her she can sell that to start over.

41
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,960
I don’t know, maybe start a business.

42
00:01:26,002 --> 00:01:28,129
But it’s up to her.

43
00:01:28,463 --> 00:01:29,589
I know her.

44
00:01:30,381 --> 00:01:32,509
She’d never ask her parents for money.

45
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:34,177
She’s too proud.

46
00:01:35,887 --> 00:01:38,765
Don't you want to keep the money for yourself instead?

47
00:01:41,309 --> 00:01:44,229
I bought that ring because Allie deserves it.

48
00:01:46,147 --> 00:01:47,857
I still believe that now.

49
00:01:49,734 --> 00:01:51,319
Even if she doesn’t want me anymore.

50
00:01:58,284 --> 00:01:59,035
[KARA] What?

51
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:01,621
Nothing. I...

52
00:02:02,163 --> 00:02:04,123
I just thought of a business idea for you.

53
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:07,043
You can sell shirts

54
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:09,295
that says,

55
00:02:09,712 --> 00:02:11,214
“I went to Siargao..."

56
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:13,633
"...and all I got was this lousy heartbreak.”

57
00:02:14,175 --> 00:02:15,552
I’ll be your first customer.

58
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:25,812
Guess the curse is real, huh?

59
00:02:27,438 --> 00:02:28,648
Damn.

60
00:02:30,108 --> 00:02:33,278
It ended my 15-year relationship with Allie.

61
00:02:35,029 --> 00:02:36,488
Don't you want to stay

62
00:02:36,489 --> 00:02:39,242
and experience the better version of the curse?

63
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:40,660
[JAO CLICKS TONGUE]

64
00:02:41,286 --> 00:02:42,452
I can’t.

65
00:02:42,453 --> 00:02:45,665
I have lots of work waiting for me in Manila.

66
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:47,417
I’m flying back in two days.

67
00:02:49,043 --> 00:02:50,420
Do you have a ride?

68
00:02:52,463 --> 00:02:53,673
No, I’m good.

69
00:02:54,382 --> 00:02:56,050
I just have

70
00:02:56,384 --> 00:02:58,094
one last thing to do

71
00:02:58,303 --> 00:02:59,345
before I go home.

72
00:03:00,263 --> 00:03:01,264
What is it?

73
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:12,358
[ALON BY JL]

74
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:25,890
[SIARGAONON] Thank you very much!

75
00:04:26,307 --> 00:04:27,558
- Here. - Thank you, sir.

76
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:29,560
Okay.

77
00:04:29,561 --> 00:04:30,603
Have you seen Jao?

78
00:04:33,189 --> 00:04:34,399
He left early.

79
00:04:35,775 --> 00:04:37,235
I think he’s buying souvenirs.

80
00:04:37,276 --> 00:04:39,529
He’s flying back to Manila tomorrow, right?

81
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:43,032
I saw him earlier.

82
00:04:43,074 --> 00:04:44,200
He said he had somewhere to go.

83
00:04:45,326 --> 00:04:46,327
Did he say where?

84
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:48,746
He didn't mention where, but...

85
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,498
he looked serious.

86
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:52,875
[HAN BIN] Do you think Jao’s okay?

87
00:04:53,084 --> 00:04:55,670
Maybe not. Because he's heartbroken...

88
00:04:55,712 --> 00:04:56,753
because of Allie.

89
00:04:56,754 --> 00:04:58,381
So I feel sorry for him.

90
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:02,427
A monk in Thailand once taught me that

91
00:05:03,011 --> 00:05:04,554
suffering is part of life.

92
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:07,140
It leads to growth and understanding.

93
00:05:07,682 --> 00:05:09,267
So, don’t feel bad for him.

94
00:05:09,517 --> 00:05:10,810
Jao will be stronger.

95
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:13,563
Wow. That’s deep, bro.

96
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:17,525
Destruction is often the first part of becoming.

97
00:05:18,192 --> 00:05:19,527
[HAN BIN] That’s also true.

98
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:23,448
It’s always dark before the sun rises again.

99
00:05:25,616 --> 00:05:27,618
Kara, you should go.

100
00:05:28,036 --> 00:05:29,328
Find where Jao is.

101
00:05:29,370 --> 00:05:30,538
He’s still our guest.

102
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:34,292
I can ask the other tricycle drivers

103
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:36,878
if they know where Sir Handsome went.

104
00:05:38,212 --> 00:05:39,422
Yes, please.

105
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,034
[WOMAN] Jao.

106
00:06:08,035 --> 00:06:09,786
[SIARGAONON] Get down from that tree.

107
00:06:09,827 --> 00:06:11,454
You might fall.

108
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:17,627
[MAN] Jao.

109
00:06:17,668 --> 00:06:19,336
[SIARGAONON] You can go back to the sea later.

110
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:21,881
You still have homework to do.

111
00:06:26,511 --> 00:06:27,511
[WOMAN] Jao.

112
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:28,679
[SIARGAONON] Enough playing.

113
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:29,972
Come home, son.

114
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:58,668
Mom. Dad.

115
00:07:00,461 --> 00:07:01,462
I’m back.

116
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:05,258
I’m sorry…

117
00:07:07,885 --> 00:07:09,720
[SIARGAONON] it took me so long to go home.

118
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:15,268
But I’m here now.

119
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:20,106
Your son’s home.

120
00:07:23,484 --> 00:07:24,485
Mom.

121
00:07:26,195 --> 00:07:27,196
Dad.

122
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:33,703
We’re not poor anymore.

123
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:41,586
I hope you’re proud of me.

124
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:44,714
[SIARGAONON] You…

125
00:07:45,464 --> 00:07:46,674
are…

126
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:49,218
my life.

127
00:07:52,847 --> 00:07:54,140
[KARA] You’re from here?

128
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:02,690
I was born here.

129
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:07,653
No wonder.

130
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:09,864
You’re from Siargao.

131
00:08:13,743 --> 00:08:15,536
Kara, these are my parents.

132
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:17,580
Mom, Dad. Kara.

133
00:08:18,789 --> 00:08:19,790
Hello.

134
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:21,876
Uh...

135
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:24,253
I didn’t mean to

136
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,297
lie to your son.

137
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:28,883
I hope you don’t haunt me.

138
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:36,224
[KARA] It’s your mom’s birthday?

139
00:08:36,557 --> 00:08:37,350
Yeah.

140
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,310
Actually, we have the same birthday.

141
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:41,562
Happy birthday.

142
00:08:41,604 --> 00:08:42,396
Thank you.

143
00:08:46,651 --> 00:08:47,817
Want to walk around?

144
00:08:47,818 --> 00:08:49,320
I want to show you something.

145
00:08:57,578 --> 00:08:58,913
[JAO] Let’s hang out here.

146
00:09:09,131 --> 00:09:10,675
Nothing has changed.

147
00:09:25,189 --> 00:09:26,565
[KARA] What are you doing?

148
00:09:27,316 --> 00:09:29,318
My mom taught me

149
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:31,779
that whenever I want to be happy,

150
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:35,574
I should draw beautiful things

151
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:36,909
in the sky.

152
00:09:37,994 --> 00:09:38,995
So...

153
00:09:39,912 --> 00:09:41,539
just in case I forget them,

154
00:09:42,373 --> 00:09:43,874
all I have to do is look at the sky,

155
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:46,085
and I'll remember them again.

156
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:48,796
What did you see?

157
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:52,842
Waves.

158
00:09:54,343 --> 00:09:56,721
What’s in the sea is also in the sky.

159
00:10:00,599 --> 00:10:03,102
Our old house

160
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:07,231
was about a five-minute walk to the closest village.

161
00:10:08,316 --> 00:10:10,943
Everything you see here?

162
00:10:13,779 --> 00:10:15,239
I grew up around all of it.

163
00:10:15,781 --> 00:10:17,783
Do you see that lighthouse?

164
00:10:18,826 --> 00:10:19,660
When I was a kid,

165
00:10:19,661 --> 00:10:21,078
I’d always climb it

166
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:24,582
whenever my dad went out fishing.

167
00:10:25,374 --> 00:10:26,292
From up there,

168
00:10:26,542 --> 00:10:29,045
I could see how far he’d gone.

169
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:31,672
[KARA] It must have been nice growing up here.

170
00:10:31,964 --> 00:10:32,965
I’m jealous.

171
00:10:33,215 --> 00:10:34,300
[JAO CHUCKLES]

172
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:37,345
We were happy, even if life was simple.

173
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:40,598
You were happy because life was simple.

174
00:10:43,559 --> 00:10:44,935
As long as no one gets sick.

175
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:49,607
[WAVES CRASHING]

176
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:54,278
I was ten when...

177
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,572
my dad got tuberculosis.

178
00:10:57,907 --> 00:11:00,117
My mom had to work twice as hard.

179
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:02,995
She processed coconuts during the day,

180
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:05,039
then at night she does laundry service.

181
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:07,291
Meanwhile,

182
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,085
I’d take on odd jobs after school.

183
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:13,923
But my favorite was selling snacks to my classmates.

184
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:18,427
There was one time I was walking home

185
00:11:18,469 --> 00:11:19,595
along that shoreline.

186
00:11:20,429 --> 00:11:23,557
I made 120 pesos that day.

187
00:11:23,974 --> 00:11:25,726
See those waves?

188
00:11:25,976 --> 00:11:28,521
I was lost in thought when...

189
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:31,315
one crashed into me, and I dropped my money.

190
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:33,067
Of course, I rushed to grab it.

191
00:11:33,109 --> 00:11:34,568
Good thing it landed on the shore.

192
00:11:35,778 --> 00:11:37,697
But I lost five pesos!

193
00:11:37,738 --> 00:11:39,740
What a waste of five pesos!

194
00:11:41,992 --> 00:11:43,285
I never found it.

195
00:11:44,912 --> 00:11:48,416
That’s when I realized…

196
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:49,750
when...

197
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:52,002
someone in your family is sick,

198
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:55,381
every peso matters.

199
00:11:58,384 --> 00:11:59,969
That’s why my dad,

200
00:12:00,886 --> 00:12:03,180
even when there's a storm,

201
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:06,642
he'd be so stubborn, he would still go fishing.

202
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:10,563
One night,

203
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,648
he went anyway,

204
00:12:12,690 --> 00:12:14,817
even though Mom begged him not to.

205
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:16,527
Then...

206
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:19,613
his boat capsized. It was just a small one.

207
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:24,410
After my dad died,

208
00:12:24,994 --> 00:12:26,829
things got even harder.

209
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:29,832
My mom had to...

210
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:32,083
sell a kidney...

211
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:33,085
Sorry.

212
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:34,086
[JAO SNIFFS]

213
00:12:34,128 --> 00:12:35,129
Sorry, Kara.

214
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:36,922
Then…

215
00:12:37,631 --> 00:12:39,967
she got an infection, and

216
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:42,344
there were complications.

217
00:12:42,636 --> 00:12:44,638
We couldn't afford treatment, so…

218
00:12:46,849 --> 00:12:48,559
we lost her, too.

219
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:54,523
Sorry.

220
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:55,733
[JAO CHUCKLES]

221
00:12:55,774 --> 00:12:57,776
You’ve really been through a lot.

222
00:12:59,236 --> 00:13:00,362
It’s fine.

223
00:13:00,821 --> 00:13:03,824
I actually really appreciate this time, Kara.

224
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:07,661
I never talk about this with my friends in Manila.

225
00:13:08,537 --> 00:13:11,457
Nobody knows the island boy side of me.

226
00:13:13,375 --> 00:13:15,920
It feels good to finally talk about it because

227
00:13:16,504 --> 00:13:18,088
it helps me heal.

228
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:25,638
[HAN BIN] Pearl?

229
00:13:26,555 --> 00:13:27,889
You wish, Pearl.

230
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:28,974
- As if I’d ever… - [HAN BIN] Pearl?

231
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:31,644
…get an international scholarship.

232
00:13:31,685 --> 00:13:32,645
Pearl.

233
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:37,650
- Boo! - Oh, my god!

234
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:41,362
Sir Han! You scared me!

235
00:13:41,403 --> 00:13:43,197
I've been calling you thrice already!

236
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:44,240
What are you looking at?

237
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:46,032
- Nothing. - Here you go.

238
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:46,742
Wow!

239
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:49,370
Freshly-made kinilaw a la Carol.

240
00:13:49,787 --> 00:13:51,789
Oh, wow!

241
00:13:52,540 --> 00:13:53,499
Try it.

242
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:54,792
[HAN BIN] Let me try!

243
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:56,168
[HAN BIN GRUNTS]

244
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:58,420
Okay. You try.

245
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:06,136
[HAN BIN MOANS]

246
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:07,887
This is so delicious!

247
00:14:07,888 --> 00:14:09,890
-Really? -You really know your food.

248
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:10,933
[QUINITO] Of course!

249
00:14:11,141 --> 00:14:14,353
And all thanks to Pearl for sharing her mom's recipe.

250
00:14:14,395 --> 00:14:17,523
And thank you for making it extra spicy for me.

251
00:14:18,607 --> 00:14:20,609
- I'll try it, okay? - Yeah.

252
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:23,821
[PEARL COUGHS]

253
00:14:25,072 --> 00:14:25,823
Hold on.

254
00:14:26,490 --> 00:14:27,741
[PEARL COUGHS] Wait.

255
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:29,868
- Too spicy! - Wait. Are you okay?

256
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:32,079
-Yeah... -I’ll give you milk!

257
00:14:32,663 --> 00:14:34,665
[PEARL COUGHING]

258
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:37,084
- Pearl, are you okay? - No!

259
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:40,921
- [PEARL GROANS] - Here.

260
00:14:44,216 --> 00:14:46,884
You know Pearl, you really are so cute.

261
00:14:46,885 --> 00:14:48,470
You're the only Siargaonon I know

262
00:14:48,512 --> 00:14:50,598
who can’t handle spicy food.

263
00:14:50,639 --> 00:14:51,599
[PEARL GROANS]

264
00:14:55,352 --> 00:14:56,770
You okay, Han Bin?

265
00:14:56,854 --> 00:14:58,606
Yeah, I'm okay. I'm just…

266
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:01,066
feeling the kick.

267
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:02,526
Well, I guess,

268
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:05,195
I made it too spicy if it's too much for a Korean.

269
00:15:05,821 --> 00:15:06,904
No, not really.

270
00:15:06,905 --> 00:15:08,198
I can take the heat.

271
00:15:09,074 --> 00:15:11,994
But please make sure Pearl doesn't suffer again.

272
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:15,831
I'm sorry, Pearl.

273
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:19,460
[PEARL] No, it’s okay. It’s really good!

274
00:15:19,501 --> 00:15:22,211
Just go easy on the spice next time, okay?

275
00:15:22,212 --> 00:15:23,672
It’s a little too spicy.

276
00:15:23,922 --> 00:15:25,591
But thanks anyway.

277
00:15:28,552 --> 00:15:30,638
- Thank you, sir. - Yeah.

278
00:15:31,221 --> 00:15:32,598
You want?

279
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:38,145
- So good. - It's spicy, I told you.

280
00:15:38,187 --> 00:15:40,439
Is it good? Oh, you’re sweating.

281
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:41,440
No, not yet.

282
00:15:41,482 --> 00:15:43,484
[WAVES CRASHING]

283
00:15:43,942 --> 00:15:45,944
So, that’s how I ended up

284
00:15:46,278 --> 00:15:48,280
an orphan.

285
00:15:48,989 --> 00:15:50,991
I wandered all over the island.

286
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:53,535
Don't you have other relatives?

287
00:15:53,869 --> 00:15:56,372
No. I was an only child.

288
00:15:56,955 --> 00:15:58,957
Everyone else lived far away.

289
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:04,797
How did you get by?

290
00:16:05,589 --> 00:16:07,549
I’d ask the neighbors for food.

291
00:16:08,884 --> 00:16:10,928
Eventually,

292
00:16:11,637 --> 00:16:15,099
I got too embarrassed, so I went to General Luna.

293
00:16:16,016 --> 00:16:19,520
I wandered around there, too.

294
00:16:20,312 --> 00:16:23,148
But nothing came of it because back then,

295
00:16:23,565 --> 00:16:26,694
tourism wasn’t what it is today.

296
00:16:26,985 --> 00:16:28,487
Luckily,

297
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:32,366
my dad’s cousin from Cebu found out.

298
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:37,204
They took me in, got me a scholarship,

299
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:39,373
and sent me to school in Manila.

300
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:51,635
I hated being poor here, Kara.

301
00:16:57,015 --> 00:16:59,518
Poverty took my parents away from me.

302
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:07,276
It took my childhood, too.

303
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:11,196
It died here with them.

304
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:18,662
Being poor is hard.

305
00:17:27,212 --> 00:17:28,213
Sorry.

306
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:30,882
Anyway…

307
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:32,885
When I boarded the ferry

308
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:35,012
to leave Siargao,

309
00:17:37,931 --> 00:17:39,016
I told myself…

310
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:41,560
I swore...

311
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:46,690
I'd never come back, no matter what.

312
00:17:49,693 --> 00:17:50,694
But,

313
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:52,696
I'm here again.

314
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:55,282
I don't know.

315
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:09,463
[KARA] You’ve been through so much.

316
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:15,385
But, I believe everything happened

317
00:18:16,678 --> 00:18:17,971
for a reason.

318
00:18:19,431 --> 00:18:21,809
And I'm glad you’ve come so far, Jao.

319
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:26,855
Thanks, Kara.

320
00:18:47,751 --> 00:18:48,961
[KARA] Happy birthday, Jao.

321
00:18:49,503 --> 00:18:50,504
Make a wish.

322
00:18:50,879 --> 00:18:52,005
Make it a good one.

323
00:18:52,422 --> 00:18:53,966
Happy birthday to your mom, too.

324
00:18:54,299 --> 00:18:57,135
[JAO] I know what my mom would wish for.

325
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:01,014
Mom. Dad.

326
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:04,810
[SIARGAONON] I’m back at our beach.

327
00:19:05,018 --> 00:19:06,687
You seem like a different person.

328
00:19:10,315 --> 00:19:11,817
Let me help you out, brother.

329
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:13,902
[QUINITO] Can I ask you a question?

330
00:19:14,069 --> 00:19:14,903
Yes.

331
00:19:14,904 --> 00:19:16,029
Do you like Pearl?

332
00:19:16,238 --> 00:19:16,947
Oh.

333
00:19:19,032 --> 00:19:20,534
It's up to Pearl.

334
00:19:21,034 --> 00:19:22,035
Not you.

335
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:24,287
We could have been friends from the start.

336
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:25,539
But you were so rude.

337
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:26,540
Wow.

338
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:29,084
So, which brings me to my question.

339
00:19:30,168 --> 00:19:32,254
How’d you end up in Siargao?
